{
  "texts": [
    "The underlying phenomena is called \"mission drift\" [66].The extent to which advising the board of directors or senior management would reduce societal risks depends on many different factors.",
    "It would be easier if the ethics board has a direct communication channel to the board of directors, ideally to a dedicated risk committee.",
    "It would also be easier if the board of directors is able to do something about risks.",
    "They need risk-related expertise and governance structures to exercise their power (e.g.",
    "a chief risk officer [CRO] as a single point of accountability)."
  ]
}